topLevelComment.text: Looks dope man. question I have is, messages and calls, apple maps all work correctly with iphone? Also, the HVAC‚Ä¶ for steering wheel heating & the seats, all still fully functional?
topLevelComment.author: @BehindMyVisor

replies.text:
Messages, calls, maps all work. This is just a pretty frontend for CarPlay, so it'll behave like any other CarPlay device.

All the HVAC/heated seats etc work fine. I don't have heated steering wheel on my Q, but I haven't heard anyone complain or report it not working for them.

The only 2 things that don't work on mine are:¬†
1) call button on the steering wheel doesn't map to anything, and¬†
2) the voice command button maps to a weird voice app that I uninstalled
replies.author: @SquareWheelsAuto

topLevelComment.text: I have been thinking seriously about the system for a few months, but have heard mixed reviews. Has there been any recent firmware updates that clean up the user interface?
topLevelComment.author: @thomasturner5742

replies.text:
Nope. If the UI bugs you, know that you can run ANY Android launcher on these things that allow you lots of flexibility and theming. Nova launcher and Car launcher pro are 2 great options I tried.

There's also the Sergey firmware which takes these things to another level with themes that incorporate telemetry from the vehicle (compass, speed and Ron meeters, etc)
